snippet: FIFA’s president filed the complaint with Switzerland’s attorney general on the recommendation of the judge who heads the organization’s ethics committee.
abstract: Soccer Roundup; FIFA turns over report from World Cup corruption inquiry to Swiss authorities due to suspicion that investigators had uncovered criminal activity; move follows recommendation of Hans-Joachim Eckert, German judge who reviewed report; other soccer news noted.
lead_paragraph: FIFA’s president filed the complaint with Switzerland’s attorney general on the recommendation of the judge who heads the organization’s ethics committee.

headline.main: FIFA Turns Over Report on World Cup Bidding to Swiss
headline.print_headline: FIFA Turns Over World Cup Bid Report to Swiss
